- Generalising the `isThreeAlikeRunes` guard to a multi-block computation (`floor(runeCount/3)`): rejected as speculative triangulation. The 4-runes test was the negative confirmation of the existing exactly-3 guard, not a forcing test for generalisation. The 7-runes test (cycle 10) is the forcing test that will drive that change.
- Extracting `isThreeAlikeRunes` to a named predicate function: rejected (used once, inlining preserves locality — cycle-8 precedent).
- Renaming `isThreeAlikeRunes`: name still accurate after the negative-case confirmation.
- Inlining `rawBasePrice` into the ternary: rejected, reduce is verbose enough to merit a name.

